	<h2 id="key-takeaways">Key takeaways</h2>
	<p>
		Design patterns provide practical methods for implementing low-resource optimisation strategies.
	</p>
	<p>
		By structuring pages around summary-first layouts, lazy loading, lightweight navigation, static entry points,
		and fallback modes, developers can ensure that applications remain accessible and efficient across a wide range
		of network conditions.
	</p>
	<p>
		Applying these patterns improves performance, reduces bandwidth usage, and ensures that digital systems remain
		usable even in constrained environments.
	</p>

